Covid 19 Dashboard

About Covid-19¶

Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) time series listing confirmed cases, reported deaths and reported recoveries. Data is disaggregated by country. Coronavirus disease (COVID-19) is caused by the Severe acute respiratory syndrome Coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) and has had a worldwide effect. On March 11 2020, the World Health Organization (WHO) declared it a pandemic, pointing to the over 118,000 cases of the Coronavirus illness in over 110 countries and territories around the world at the time.

About Data¶

This dataset includes time series data tracking the number of people affected by COVID-19 worldwide, including:

  1. Confirmed tested cases of Coronavirus infection
  2. The number of people who have reportedly died while sick with Coronavirus
  3. The number of people who have reportedly recovered from it

Data is in CSV format and updated daily. It is sourced from this upstream repository maintained by the amazing team at Johns Hopkins University Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) who have been doing a great public service from an early point by collating data from around the world.

Note:I was working on 2020-09-22 on this dataset, thus all the results and visualizations are from 2020-01-22 upto 2020-09-21.

Visualize Global Spread of Covid 19¶

Observations

We can see above map of whole world, and it is changing from first covid confirmed case date to the present date. At first there were 77.2k cases in China and almost zero cases in other countries. But as soon we start moving our Date slider towards right, then situation started changing for other countries too. We can see at present date most number of cases are in USA, India and Brazil.

Also there is a play button on date slider, which changes dates automatically and reflects the confirmed cases in map accordingly.

Visualize Global Deaths due to Covid 19¶

Observations

Above map shows deaths due to covid 19 with date slider. At first there were 2.5k deaths in China and almost zero in other countires. But as soon we start moving our Date slider towards right, then death cases started increasing in other countries too. We can see at present date most number of deaths are in USA, Brazil and India which is no surpise as cases are scaling in these countries day by day.

Now we want to calculate Maximum infection rate for all of the countries which is at what rate covid spreads in different countries.

We are going to see how intensive the spread of covid virus has been in each of the countries. We are gonna use a bar chart to see the spread in different countries. For doing this, we need to calculate a measure which can describe how intensive or massive spread of virus has been in the country. A good measure for that is the maximum infection rate or in layman terms rate of maximum number of confirmed cases over a period of time such as 24 hours.

Visualize Maximum Infection Rate of each country¶

Observations

We can see Infection Rates for different countries in above line graph. We can select different countries from legend and compare their Maximum Infection Rate easily.

Top 20 countries which has maximum infection rate¶

Observations

We can see from above bar graph Top 20 countries which has Maximum infection rate starting from India with 97.8k followed by US with 77.25k then Brazil with 69k and so on.

Observations

We can see in above graph covid cases have been increasing since May but on the other hand the infection rate is constant.

Impact of National Lockdown on Covid 19 transmission in India¶

On 25 March 2020, the government of India under Prime Minister Narendra Modi imposed a national quarantine, restricting the movement of the population except for necessity, work, and health circumstances, in response to the growing pandemic of COVID-19 in the country.

Visualize Infection Rate Before and After Lockdown in India¶

Observations

At the start of the lockdown there were not many cases. As soon the lockdown imposed cases started increasing and also the lockdown gets lifted too soon in India which is why the cases rose day by day. Thus there was no such impact on Covid 19 cases of lockdown in India

Visualize Infection Rate v/s Death Rate in India¶

Observations

There is no such impact of lockdown on Death rate in India as it is constant which means it is neither increasing nor decreasing. It implies same number of people are dying everyday due to Covid 19.

Visualize Confirmed v/s Deaths v/s Recovered cases of Covid 19 in India¶

Observations

From above graph we can see both Confirmed and Recovered cases are going parallelly which means the rate of COnfirmed cases is same as that of Recovered cases thus it is a good behaviour. And also Deaths are not increasing as it is constant, it just got a bit increased in Late august.
